# Project Integrity

## Directory Structure — Never Break

```
web/
  src/                # React/Vite dashboard source
  public/             # static assets and derived dashboard data
ml/
  mlmodel.py          # pipeline: load, encode, train, evaluate, infer, save
  models/             # one file per model class (inherits BaseModel)
params/
  ml_params.yaml      # ML config (model, optuna, threshold)
dataset/              # raw hackathon data, read-only, never modify
dataset_cleaned/      # preprocessed parquet files, read-only
notebooks/            # one per author/experiment
outputs/
  res_perf/           # performance artifacts (metrics, plots, feature importances)
  submissions/        # submission CSVs only
```

## Rules

- `dataset/` and `dataset_cleaned/` are **read-only** — never write, move, or delete files there
- `ml/mlmodel.py` is the single ML pipeline entrypoint (load data, encode, train, evaluate, infer, save)
- New models go in `ml/models/` following `BaseModel` interface
- `params/ml_params.yaml` stays minimal — no hardcoded paths elsewhere
- Submissions always go to `outputs/submissions/`
- Performance artifacts (metrics, plots, feature importances) go to `outputs/res_perf/`
- Never commit trained model artifacts (`.joblib`) — already in `.gitignore`
- Category encoding is fitted on train and applied to eval to avoid mismatch
